         <div type="translation">
            <p>Castor, Pollux, Amycus</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The incident depicted does not seem to be otherwise recorded. In known versions of his story Amykos, the son of Poseidon and a nymph Melia, as king of the Bebrykes in Bithynia challenged vistors to his kingdom to box. When the Argonauts visited, Polydeukes (Pollux) accepted the challenge and killed him with a blow to the elbow (Hyginus, Fabuulae 17; Apollodorus 1.9.20).</p>
         </div>
